WEBVTT

00:00.206 --> 00:02.781
<i>Kids, in the winter of 2010,</i>

00:02.795 --> 00:05.897
<i>we had a new addition
to our little group-- Zoey.</i>

00:05.898 --> 00:08.366
<i>Zoey was married to...
The Captain.</i>

00:08.367 --> 00:10.768
Boys! Great to see you!

00:10.769 --> 00:11.869
Looking smart.

00:11.870 --> 00:13.738
Have a wonderful time
tonight, okay?

00:13.739 --> 00:16.140
Okay.

00:16.140 --> 00:17.842
That man is terrifying.

00:17.843 --> 00:20.344
Everything he said was nice,
but I am profoundly scared.

00:20.345 --> 00:22.113
Keep smiling.
He can still see us.

00:22.114 --> 00:23.347
(all murmuring)

00:23.348 --> 00:25.283
<i>NARRATOR: There was
just something about him.</i>

00:25.284 --> 00:28.019
<i>We couldn't put
our finger on it until...</i>

00:28.020 --> 00:29.654
I figured it out!

00:30.589 --> 00:32.790
I know what's so creepy
about The Captain.

00:32.791 --> 00:33.724
Okay.

00:35.561 --> 00:36.994
(all scream)
Yeah.

00:36.995 --> 00:38.162
I snapped this
photo of him

00:38.163 --> 00:39.664
last time he dropped off Zoey.

00:39.665 --> 00:40.932
Observe.

00:40.933 --> 00:43.034
The bottom half
of his face... is smiling.

00:43.035 --> 00:44.702
LILY: Oh. Look,
he seems happy.

00:44.703 --> 00:46.904
Seems like a nice guy.

00:46.905 --> 00:48.005
(all murmur happily)

00:48.006 --> 00:50.174
But the top half of his face...

00:50.175 --> 00:50.908
(all gasp)

00:50.909 --> 00:52.109
...wants to murder you!

00:52.110 --> 00:54.111
Cheerful.

00:54.112 --> 00:55.613
(all screaming)
Wants to murder you.

00:55.614 --> 00:57.248
No. Cheerful.

00:57.249 --> 00:58.983
(all scream)
Wants to murder you.

00:58.984 --> 01:01.252
Now, hold on.
Let me ask him a question.

01:01.253 --> 01:04.422
Captain,
what do you think of ice cream?

01:04.423 --> 01:05.756
Oh, he loves it!

01:05.757 --> 01:07.758
Captain, what do you
think of rainy days?

01:07.759 --> 01:10.027
(gasps) Whoa, he hates them.

01:10.028 --> 01:12.530
Captain, quick question:

01:12.531 --> 01:14.398
How do you feel about
the Jonas Brothers? Ooh.

01:14.399 --> 01:15.600
Ooh.
Ooh.

01:18.203 --> 01:19.470
What-What is that?

01:19.471 --> 01:21.172
I don't get it.
I don't get it.

01:21.173 --> 01:23.941
He hates that he loves them.

01:23.942 --> 01:25.309
(all murmur):
Ah!

01:25.310 --> 01:29.146
<font color="#ffff00">Captioning sponsored by</font>
<font color="#ffff00">20th CENTURY FOX TELEVISION,</font>

01:29.147 --> 01:33.150
<font color="#ffff00">CBS</font>

01:33.151 --> 01:37.388
<font color="#ffff00">and TOYOTA.</font>

01:38.123 --> 01:39.423
Great. Okay.

01:39.424 --> 01:40.858
Hey, guys, Zoey just told me

01:40.859 --> 01:42.894
about this great Frank Lloyd
Wright retrospective tonight.

01:42.895 --> 01:44.095
Who's in?

01:44.096 --> 01:46.130
Sorry, I'm, uh, I...

01:46.131 --> 01:47.932
I- I don't know,
washing my hair.

01:47.933 --> 01:48.699
Running the water.

01:48.700 --> 01:49.800
Holding the towel.

01:49.801 --> 01:50.935
And I'll be home

01:50.936 --> 01:52.203
trying to get over the fact

01:52.204 --> 01:54.038
that no one invited me
to the big hair washing party.

01:54.039 --> 01:56.340
All right, fine.
Guess it'll just be me and Zoey.

01:56.341 --> 01:58.209
Oh, wait.
Just the two of you?

01:58.210 --> 02:00.111
Tread lightly, Mosby.

02:00.112 --> 02:01.045
Any time

02:01.046 --> 02:02.346
a single guy hangs out

02:02.347 --> 02:03.481
with a married woman,

02:03.482 --> 02:05.283
there are rules
that must be followed.

02:05.284 --> 02:06.951
Rule number one...

02:06.952 --> 02:08.452
Don't use
the husband's condoms.

02:08.453 --> 02:10.086
That's just rude.

02:10.088 --> 02:12.657
Rule number one:

02:12.658 --> 02:15.593
don't go anywhere
that has candles.

02:15.594 --> 02:17.962
Excuse me, Captain,
how do you feel

02:17.963 --> 02:20.998
about Ted and Zoey having
an intimate chat by candlelight?

02:20.999 --> 02:22.166
Mm-hmm...

02:22.167 --> 02:23.301
(yelling)

02:23.302 --> 02:25.636
It'll be the last dinner
they ever have.

02:26.271 --> 02:27.939
Rule number two:

02:27.940 --> 02:29.373
No sharing food.
Hmm.

02:29.374 --> 02:31.943
In fact, anything involving
saliva is off-limits.

02:31.944 --> 02:34.578
Toothbrushes,
thermometers, lipstick.

02:34.579 --> 02:35.746
Well, if I can't share
her lipstick,

02:35.747 --> 02:36.881
there's really no point
in even going.

02:36.882 --> 02:39.450
And the most
important rule of all...

02:39.451 --> 02:42.119
Lubricant is public
property. (Robin groans)

02:42.120 --> 02:42.853
Please.

02:42.854 --> 02:44.388
No lying to the spouse

02:44.389 --> 02:46.490
about anything you do.

02:46.491 --> 02:47.625
Why would anyone lie?

02:47.626 --> 02:48.759
Look, Zoey and I
are just friends.

02:48.760 --> 02:50.061
If there was anything more
than that,

02:50.062 --> 02:51.262
I wouldn't hang out with her.

02:51.263 --> 02:53.164
Lily's right, Ted.
Once you're married,

02:53.165 --> 02:54.498
it's very hard to be friends

02:54.499 --> 02:57.034
with a single person of the
opposite sex. ROBIN: Yeah.

02:57.035 --> 02:58.502
Unless you're old friends,
which is why

02:58.503 --> 03:00.504
I can hang out
with Marshall whenever I want.

03:00.505 --> 03:01.605
Right, Marsh Madness?

03:01.606 --> 03:02.974
No doubt, Robo Cop.

03:04.343 --> 03:05.743
You two never hang out alone.

03:05.744 --> 03:07.712
You just made up those nicknames
right now.

03:07.713 --> 03:08.980
I guess it's true.

03:08.981 --> 03:11.148
You and I never really
hang out alone.

03:11.149 --> 03:13.718
Well, let's. Let's have dinner
together, just the two of us.

03:13.719 --> 03:14.986
Oh! Sweet.

03:14.987 --> 03:16.921
No candles.

03:16.922 --> 03:18.990
BOTH:
No candles.

03:18.991 --> 03:21.125
Lily, I guess that leaves
just you and me. Want to hang?

03:21.126 --> 03:23.160
<i>NARRATOR: And then Lily
said something to Barney</i>

03:23.161 --> 03:25.129
<i>that insulted every fiber
of his being.</i>

03:25.130 --> 03:26.564
Nah.

03:26.565 --> 03:28.065
(gasps)

03:28.066 --> 03:30.534
<i>NARRATOR: Wait. No. It had
to be more than just, "Nah."</i>

03:30.535 --> 03:31.669
<i>Oh, I think she said...</i>

03:31.670 --> 03:35.906
You're a big...
stupid octopus head!

03:35.907 --> 03:37.108
(gasps)

03:37.109 --> 03:38.542
<i>NARRATOR:
No, that doesn't make sense.</i>

03:38.543 --> 03:41.145
<i>Okay, hang on.
What did she say?</i>

03:41.146 --> 03:45.916
<i>She said, um, uh...</i>

03:45.917 --> 03:48.819
<i>To be honest kids, I'm having
a little trouble remembering</i>

03:48.820 --> 03:50.521
<i>exactly what their fight
was about.</i>

03:50.522 --> 03:52.156
<i>Hey, it was 20 years ago!</i>

03:52.157 --> 03:53.324
<i>I'll remember.</i>

03:53.325 --> 03:54.759
<i>Anyway, the next night...</i>

03:54.760 --> 03:57.228
Well, Lily,
you were right.

03:57.229 --> 04:00.531
Something weird happened
with Zoey last night.

04:00.532 --> 04:03.834
(phone plays "Anchors Aweigh")
Oh, that's the Captain.

04:03.835 --> 04:05.703
Yes, I call my husband
The Captain,

04:05.704 --> 04:08.906
but that is the only concession
I make to his seafaring ways.

04:08.907 --> 04:10.341
Hang on.

04:10.342 --> 04:11.709
Ahoy.

04:11.710 --> 04:14.445
I'm just out with friends.

04:14.446 --> 04:16.313
Friends. Plural.

04:16.314 --> 04:18.548
Like-Like there was more
than one of me.

04:18.550 --> 04:19.784
Ew! Ew!

04:19.785 --> 04:22.553
She lied
to her husband? Uh-oh.

04:22.554 --> 04:24.355
So, what did you do?

04:24.356 --> 04:27.792
Uh, Zoey, um, did you just say
you were out with friends?

04:27.793 --> 04:29.927
Yeah. The Captain's
on his way home from Milan.

04:29.928 --> 04:31.595
He can get a little jealous
sometimes,

04:31.596 --> 04:33.697
so I didn't want
to make him worry.

04:34.533 --> 04:35.499
Is that okay?

04:35.500 --> 04:37.368
It's totally okay.

04:37.369 --> 04:39.737
It's not okay! I didn't
really think it was okay!

04:39.738 --> 04:42.373
Pur-leez! You lie to
your husband all the time.

04:42.374 --> 04:44.642
"Uh, uh, that shirt
looks great on you""

04:44.643 --> 04:46.444
"I love your mom""

04:46.445 --> 04:48.879
"I never fantasize about
Barney when we're doing it""

04:48.880 --> 04:51.415
Sound familiar, Pinocchio?

04:51.416 --> 04:52.683
(scoffs)

04:52.684 --> 04:53.884
What's wrong
with this shirt?

04:53.885 --> 04:56.053
TED:
Lily, ruling.

04:56.054 --> 04:57.388
Do I have to stop

04:57.389 --> 04:58.923
hanging out with Zoey?

04:58.924 --> 05:01.025
No, you just need
to spend time

05:01.026 --> 05:03.094
with her
and The Captain together.

05:03.095 --> 05:04.929
If you're friends
with the both of them,

05:04.930 --> 05:06.363
then there's not a problem.

05:06.364 --> 05:08.766
Actually, I do have a standing
invitation from The Captain

05:08.767 --> 05:11.235
to go for a ride with them
on his boat.

05:11.236 --> 05:14.238
Great. So go make nice
with Captain Creepy,

05:14.239 --> 05:15.439
and problem solved.

05:15.440 --> 05:17.541
<i>NARRATOR:
The next night,</i>

05:17.542 --> 05:19.310
<i>Marshall and Robin went
to dinner,</i>

05:19.311 --> 05:20.878
<i>just the two of them.</i>

05:20.879 --> 05:22.046
<i>Now historically,</i>

05:22.047 --> 05:24.081
<i>they had three solid
conversation topics:</i>

05:24.082 --> 05:25.416
<i>cold weather...</i>

05:25.417 --> 05:28.185
December chill-- so great.

05:28.186 --> 05:29.820
Totally.

05:31.423 --> 05:33.357
<i>NARRATOR:
...sports...</i>

05:33.358 --> 05:35.392
Did you catch

05:35.393 --> 05:37.862
the game last night?

05:37.863 --> 05:40.931
Yeah. Nail-biter.

05:41.833 --> 05:45.002
<i>NARRATOR:
...and cold weather sports.</i>

05:45.003 --> 05:46.804
You know what's fun?
Mm.

05:46.805 --> 05:48.172
Is cold weather sports.

05:48.173 --> 05:50.141
They are fun.

05:50.142 --> 05:53.744
<i>NARRATOR: They blew through
them all in the first 16 seconds.</i>

05:53.745 --> 05:56.080
<i>ROBIN:
Man, this is awkward.</i>

05:56.081 --> 05:58.482
<i>MARSHALL:
She's giving me nothing!</i>

05:58.483 --> 06:00.751
<i>He's just staring at me!</i>

06:00.752 --> 06:02.653
<i>She's just staring at me!</i>

06:02.654 --> 06:04.922
<i>It's making me nervous.</i>

06:04.923 --> 06:06.924
<i>Great, now my left eye
is twitching.</i>

06:06.925 --> 06:08.559
<i>Marshall, it's cool.</i>

06:08.560 --> 06:10.227
<i>She doesn't see it.</i>

06:10.228 --> 06:13.264
<i>What the hell's going on
with his eye?</i>

06:13.265 --> 06:15.499
<i>Am I supposed to not talk
about that?</i>

06:15.500 --> 06:19.069
<i>Great, now
my right eye is doing it.</i>

06:21.706 --> 06:23.340
Can I get you two some drinks?

06:23.341 --> 06:25.209
Lots of drinks.
Oh, so many drinks.

06:25.210 --> 06:28.112
<i>NARRATOR: That same night, Barney
and Lily were still fighting</i>

06:28.113 --> 06:29.647
<i>about, um... something.</i>

06:29.648 --> 06:31.849
<i>Or was it that other thing?</i>

06:31.850 --> 06:33.284
Barney.
Save it, Lily.

06:33.285 --> 06:35.553
I am still mad at you for...

06:35.554 --> 06:38.656
something, and for
that other thing.

06:38.657 --> 06:41.125
Look, I'm sorry
I hurt your feelings.

06:41.126 --> 06:42.626
But let's be honest.

06:42.627 --> 06:44.828
You've been super
sensitive lately.

06:44.829 --> 06:46.964
(crying):
No, I haven't!

06:46.965 --> 06:49.366
God, how can you say that?!

06:49.367 --> 06:51.168
Watch out!
(yells)

06:51.169 --> 06:53.404
NARRATOR:
Wait. They were on the street.

06:53.405 --> 06:55.940
Watch out!
Oh!

06:55.941 --> 06:58.909
Wow. Thanks, Lily.

06:58.910 --> 07:01.278
You saved me.

07:01.279 --> 07:03.047
You saved us.

07:03.748 --> 07:06.984
Look, I know
you didn't mean

07:06.985 --> 07:10.087
whatever it was
you said that made me so mad.

07:10.088 --> 07:12.323
I think I probably didn't.

07:12.324 --> 07:15.793
<i>NARRATOR: And just like
that, the fight was over.</i>

07:15.794 --> 07:18.762
<i>You know, kids,
friendship is funny sometimes.</i>

07:18.763 --> 07:20.130
Wait.

07:20.131 --> 07:23.133
I still can't resist
getting one last shot in.

07:23.134 --> 07:24.602
(gasps)

07:24.603 --> 07:27.938
<i>NARRATOR: Like I said, the
fight was just getting started.</i>

